== Test 2

In many countries, primary and secondary schools close for two months or more in the summer holidays. What is the value of long school holidays? What are the arguments in favour of shorter school holidays?]

#作文(timing: 45, words: 340, date: "2025-12-08")[In many countries, mine included, schools close for about two months in the summer to give us the cherished "summer holidays". We also have the "winter holidays", too, though for a shorter length of time. These holidays have been taken for granted. But #issue[come to think of it][避免口语化表达], what is their value?

The first reason that comes to mind is that students need a #praise[respite][词汇丰富] from their arduous study. As the saying goes, "all work and no play makes Jack a dull boy", so the summer holidays serve as #typo[interludeds][interludes] between periods of intense study, #praise[in which][尝试使用复杂句结构] students can go abroad, to the beach, hiking or swimming, for a bit of adventure, or just some fresh air. The brain is in desperate need of a change of scene after months of immersing itself in knowledge.

#praise[What's more][自然衔接], some countries have the hottest summers on earth (think of the insane temperatures in India) and the heat becomes physically unbearable to stay in school buildings, especially if air conditioning is not available. For the same reason, adults customarily leave office to enjoy vacations in the summer, too, including teachers and school staff. In this case, summer holidays are practically mandatory.

The schools can use this time for renovations, organize teacher training, and run other #typo[repairatory][maintenance] operations that wouldn't be possible during the semesters. That's a third value.

This is all well and nice, but does the #typo[holidy][holiday] really need to last for as long as two months, and in some cases even longer? It is a valid argument that's often heard, mostly from parents. Indeed, parents do not usually have long summer holidays, and it becomes some sort of an "inconvenience", to say the least, when they have to go to work and nobody #issue[was][时态错误（应为is）。全句都在用现在时描述。] around to look after their naughty children who, left to their own devices, are prone to look for all sorts of trouble. #issue[][对“支持短假期”的论证薄弱，仅从家长角度提及“不便”，缺乏教育角度的深入分析，如学业遗忘、教育效率等。] So perhaps shorter summer holidays? #issue[My guess is][不严谨] that this proposal will meet with tremendous opposition from the students, so #issue[good luck with that :)][结尾过于随意] #issue[][结尾缺少总结段]]

